  "texts": [
    "It can accurately learn node representations rich in semantic information and deeply capture the complex relationships between nodes and the structure and feature information of the graph.",
    "Graph representation learning can be subdivided into three levels: node-level, edge-level, and graph-level representation learning according to the type of its downstream tasks (Fang et al. 2022).",
    "Among them, the key point of graph-level representation learning is to generate a low-dimensional vector representation for the whole graph, which has wide applications in bioinformatics (Zhang et al. 2021a; Kang et al. 2022; Réau et al. 2023; Wang et al. 2023a), computational chemistry (Fung et al. 2021; Reiser et al. 2022; Wen et al. 2021; Ye et al. 2020; Hu et al. 2103a), social network analysis (Fan et al. 2019; Sharma et al. 2022; Sankar et al. 2021; Guo and Wang 2020; Kumar et al. 2022), urban computing (Jiang and Luo 2022; Jin et al. 2023b; Xue et al. 2022; Hou et al. 2022), cybersecurity (Zhou et al. 2019; He et al. 2022), and other fields.",
    "Figure 1 illustrates the overall architecture of graphlevel representation learning.",
    "The early research on graph neural networks attempted to encode the whole graph by aggregating the features of representative nodes in the graph. 1 3"
